cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.CL

This paper discusses improvements to the PAM algorithm for clustering non-Euclidean data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DM (Data Mining) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses improvements to the Clara and CLARANS algorithms, which are commonly used for clustering, suggesting that cs.DB (Databases) is also a likely category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it discusses clustering text data.
